<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=4.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffe...ID=4.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
First, you want to kite the raptors on the island where they spawn.  It seems incredibly tight at first, but there is plenty of room if you know what you are doing.  The #1 reason for getting killed on Raptor isle is having to deal with unexpected adds.  There are only 3 ways this can happen:<br>
<br>
1) Your kite path goes too close to a static spawn.<br>
2) A roamer's path comes across your kite and it joins the party.<br>
3) Raptors returning from another player's blown kite happen across you while you are medding/kiting.<br>
<br>
These can all be dealt with easily, but you need to plan for them.  First of all... take the time (15-20 minutes) to study the patterns of the raptors on the isle where you will be hunting.  Find ALL the raptors.  Follow the roamer as he does his pattern. If you do this while invisible, it is completely safe. Yes, this takes time and is boring, but can easily save your life multiple times.  If it prevents just ONE death (or even a gate), you've earned your time back.  Once you know where all the spawns are, here is how you counteract the unwanted adds:<br>
<br>
1) don't bring your kite path across additional statics<br>
2) when you pull, make certain that you grab the roamers as a part of your pull.  If you are the second kiter on large isle, make certain you are done with your kite before the first kite repops.<br>
3) communicate with others doing raptors.  do a /who druid and /who wizard to find out who is in the zone and of the appropriate level.  Make certain you let them know when things have gone awry, and ask them to do the same.  Finally, when you med, be invis unless you completely trust the others at raptors.<br>
<br>
For learning to quad the raptors on the isle, start on small isle.  The only thing you really need is one long straightaway, and small isle has 2 -- one on the north beach (I always did this west to east) and one on the south beach (same -- west to east).  You can easily gather up all the raptors and do 2 circles (roughly around the building on the north side), then drag them as far to the west as you can, then do the long straight run east.  I would always stop at the &quot;plant&quot; next to where the VR spawns to do my snare.  If I got a resist, I would run around the group, then do a quick straight run from east to west and snare again.  Gather the 4 together, resnare them all, then kill at my leisure.  Once you get them snared, it is trivial to get the distance needed to do a Pillar spell.  Also, until you are VERY comfortable with the process, keep levitate up at all times.<br>
<br>
Now would be a good time to mention that my first visit to raptor isle was an ill-fated one (where I learned of their tremendous agro range).  My next couple visits involved dragging raptors to chessboard isle, and were only moderately successful.  When I finally learned the secret of kiting them on the isle itself, though, I was hooked.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>
Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utzeendao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzeen Dao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/13/01 11:48:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raptor Quad Kiting - Detailed guide</span><hr size=1> Spankda,<br>
  I kite on the small island all the time.  I grab the three static spawns (2 raptors, 1 vicious raptor) on the north side plus the wanderer.<br>
<br>
Give me a tell sometime when I'm on, and I'll show you what I do.<br>
<br>
Here is my general method:<br>
<br>
I sit over the water, north of the vicious raptor spawn, using levitate.  I have a FB earring, in case lev drops while medding.  I do this so I can watch the wanderer approach.  He's the signal to start the pull.<br>
<br>
I keep Shield of the Magi and a 'skin up, in addition to levitate and Tboots.  Refresh levitate and Tboots after every pull.<br>
<br>
When the wanderer starts coming around from my left (looking at the vicious), I start towards the island when he gets close.<br>
<br>
I use my Flux Staff to pull the wanderer (always a raptor).  Switch targets to the Vicious Raptor/Dinus and Flux him.  Then I turn to the right and run down the beach, passing close to the building.  That will aggro the raptor behind the building.  I target the other raptor on the beach and flux him.<br>
<br>
As soon as the fourth raptor aggros and turns towards me, I turn 90° to the right and head out over the water.<br>
<br>
Then I switch camera views to an external camera that is pointed back towards the island.  I want to watch the raptors.<br>
<br>
Then, two things: Make sure the building raptor is aggroed, and select the Vicious Raptor.<br>
<br>
If the building raptor isn't aggroed, I'll pick him up when I swing around.<br>
<br>
He should be aggroed, however.  Practice has told me how close to the building I need to move.<br>
<br>
Okay, all four raptors are chasing me at this point if things are going well.  If I timed it right, they are already starting to bunch up.  I'm running away from the island, and they are slowed down in the water.  I'll turn to my right a little and then start to make a circle around to my left.  This should finish the bunching up.<br>
<br>
Now I run back to the east end of the island, by where the Vicious Raptor/Dinus spawns.<br>
<br>
I cast Atol's as soon as possible.  This should snare all four raptors.  If I get a resist, I run north again, back out over the water.  Then turn and run to the west end of the island and repeat the snare on the raptor who resisted.  Then head towards the building and bunch all the raptors together.  I don't need to resnare, if all goes well.<br>
<br>
If all four didn't resist, I turn and back to the middle of the island, staying close to the shore.<br>
<br>
I can get three pillars in before reaching the west end of the island and turn around.  By the time I get back to the Vicious Raptor spawn, all the normal raptors should be dead and the Vicious in run mode (but not running due to the snare).  Sometimes things are a little different.  Depending on resists, I may have to scoot past them and run towards the middle of the island to finish.<br>
<br>
If you move too far away from any fleeing raptors, they will teleport back to the spawn point.  This Is Bad.<br>
<br>
If things go bad, I try to resnare and run to the chessboard island to camp.  Haven't had to do that in a while...<br>
<br>
You should also have enough time between killing the last raptor and the wanderer coming back around to get in a minute or two of spell practice (conjuration and divination for me).<br>
<br>
There are probably more efficient ways to pull the small island (the south spawns would let you pull the wanderer as soon as he spawns, instead of having to wait for him to wander), but this method is very safe and comfortable for me.<br>
<br>
I would be interested in more information on the big island.  I'm going to try out the couple methods listed above...<br>
<br>
pax,<br>
-Xoxxala<br>
